-- Tam Cuts 2012 Guidance for Demand Increase to 7%-9% from 8%-11%
-- B y   A d r i a n a   B r a s i l e i r o
-- 2012-04-18T03:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-18/tam-cuts-2012-guidance-for-demand-increase-to-7-9-from-8-11-.html
Tam SA (TAMM4) ,  Brazil â€™s largest airline by
market value, reduced its estimate for an increase in domestic
demand for this year to between 7 percent and 9 percent from a
previous guidance of 8 percent to 11 percent, the company said
in a regulatory filing yesterday.  The company also revised its guidance for available
seating, according to the statement. Tam said available seating
may fall as much as 2 percent this year compared with last year,
the statement added. Its previous estimate announced in January
was for an increase of as much as 2 percent, the statement also
